Zeus was therefore worshipped at Prymnessos as the giver of fruits and the increase of the earth: the epithet is not elsewhere applied to him. lt is of similar character to πλουτοδότης Jac- chos and καρποφόρος Demeter, and suggests that the Zeus ol Prymnessos ranked among the fertilising and life-giving dei· ties of the earth and the underworld.
